'''Lukáš Horníček''' (born 13 July 2002) is a Czech professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Primeira Liga]] club [[S.C. Braga|Braga]] and the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic national team]].

==Club career==
Horníček is a youth product of the academies of the Czech clubs Sokol Dobříkov and [[FK Pardubice|Pardubice]]. On 19 July 2019, he signed on a trial loan with the Portuguese club [[S.C. Braga|Braga]] for one year with an option to buy.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/zahranici/lukas-hornicek-hostovani-pardubice-braga.A190718_163446_fot_zahranici_ten|title=Brankářský talent Horníček zamířil do Portugalska. Chytat bude za Bragu|trans-title=Goalkeeping talent Horníček heads to Portugal. He'll catch for Braga|language=cs|date=2019-07-18|agency=[[Czech News Agency]]|website=iDNES.cz|access-date=2025-10-03}}</ref> On 24 July 2020, he signed permanently with Braga in what was Pardubice's biggest sale in their history.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://isport.blesk.cz/clanek/fotbal-1-liga-rocnik-2019-20/381936/nej-prestup-v-historii-pardubic-talent-definitivne-odchazi-do-portugalska.html|title=Nej přestup v historii Pardubic. Talent definitivně odchází do Portugalska|language=cs|website=iSport.cz|date=2020-07-24|access-date=2025-10-03}}</ref> He was named the best goalkeeper for the Liga Revelação 2020/21 season for Braga's youth team.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sjogadores.pt/?pt=news&op=OP_SHOW_DETAIL&id=11409|title=Lukas Hornicek é o Melhor Guarda-Redes da Liga Revelação|trans-title=Lukáš Horníček is the best goalkeeper of the Liga Revelação|website=sjogadores.pt|language=pt|date=2021-04-28|access-date=2025-10-03}}</ref> For the 2021–22 season, he was promoted to [[S.C. Braga B|Braga B]]. He made his first senior debut with Braga in a 5–0 [[Taça de Portugal]] win over Moitense, coming on as a late substitute in the 85th minute.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ojogo.pt/emdirecto/taca-portugal/direto-moitense-braga-14228177.html|title=DIRETO &#124; Moitense-Braga|website=www.ojogo.pt|date=17 October 2021 }}</ref> He made his [[Primeira Liga]] debut with Braga in a 3–2 loss to [[F.C. Famalicão|Famalicão]] on 15 May 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://portugoal.net/club-news/2587-portugoal-figure-of-the-week-banza-brace-fires-famalicao-to-top-eight-finish|title=PortuGOAL Figure of the Week: Banza brace fires Famalicão to top eight finish|website=portugoal.net|first=Jamie|last=Farr|date=2022-05-16|access-date=2025-10-03}}</ref>

==International career==
Horníček is a youth international for the Czech Republic, having represented the [[Czech Republic national under-17 football team|Czech Republic U17]]s at the [[2019 UEFA European Under-17 Championship]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://fkpardubice.cz//news/12190/Tri-nasi-hraci-vykopali-postup-na-Euro.html|title=Tři naši hráči vykopali postup na Euro!!!|website=FKPardubice.cz|language=cs|date=2019-03-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220516205756/http://fkpardubice.cz//news/12190/Tri-nasi-hraci-vykopali-postup-na-Euro.html|archive-date=2022-05-16}}</ref>

On the 31st May 2026, he made his senior debut in a 2-1 friendly win over Kosovo.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://karlobag.eu/en/sports/czech-republic-vs-kosovo-2-1-in-prague-ladra-and-hlozek-goals-in-final-home-worl-1ltoh/|title=Czech Republic vs Kosovo 2-1 in Prague, Ladra and Hložek goals in final home World Cup 2026 tune-up at Letná|date=2026-06-01}}</ref>. After the game, he was confirmed in the 26-man squad heading for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fotbal.cz/repre/finalni-nominace-reprezentace-na-mistrovstvi-sveta-2026/a24171|title=Finální nominace reprezentace na mistrovství světa 2026|trans-title=Final nominations for the 2026 World Cup|website=FOTBAL.CZ|language=cs|date=2026-05-31}}</ref>

